### 2. 
> NOTE: We have all the vertices in this way (x/z, y/z, 1).
- First we find the minimum between all the Xs, Ys and Zs. If it is negative we biuld such         Translate matrix:

    |  | | | |
    | ------ | ------- | ------ | ------ |
    1  |  0  |  0  |  min
     0  |  1  |  0  |  min
    0  |  0  |  1  |  0
    0  |  0  |  0  |  1
   
- Second we find the max between all the Xs, Ys and Zs. and then we biuld such Scale matrix
    
    |  | | | |
    | ------ | ------- | ------ | ------ |
    100/max  |  0  |  0  |  0
    0  |  100/max  |  0  |  0
    0  |  0  | 100/max  |  0
    0  |  0  |  0  |  1
- We Translate first then Scale the model, and get a model with vertices around 0-1000.

### 4. Screenshot of the GUI:
> ![banana4.png](https://dub01pap003files.storage.live.com/y4mqRdA-LecVm1inLg10_U0Yow1NiiBybLWW7DnzJMBvrhYZ5uxsoGWIwBI6-yVJqcflmCudaNW3qi5SixFZ-3r5yIpZ5FDh0gT740eTs13D-5gBMwLwf_0VdYPg6A8dD7m9TNRz23YB6YAltMaeaGjllE8m86BSTYwwPC4TB95R-E4011z-D0Xy2SHv0VoNt3R?width=1279&height=758&cropmode=none)

- Transformatiom:
First, we give each MeshModel several matrices (Scale, Translate, Rotate X, Rotate Y, Rotate Z, WORLD transform, OBJECT transform). These matrices change according to the changes we do in the GUI we build in the main. 
Each transformation OBJECT\ LOCAL and WORLD has its 3 matrices (SCALE, TRANSLATE, ROTATE). To calculate each one of the transformations we multiply the 3 matrices in the following order SRT (SCALE, ROTATE, TRANSLATE).
To get the transformation we multiply:
 WORLD transformation * OBJECT transformation
